Our Alternate Reality gaming client is hiring Software Engineers with Computer Vision experience.  This is a full time onsite role in Sunnyvale.  

https://jobs.crelate.com/portal/labineassociates/job/mvncvcyhiyj-075867/Computer_Vision_Engineer_For_AR_Gaming_Company_Sunnyvale

Tech stack includes: C++, Java, Android, C, API, NoSQL, Redis, Cassandra, ZeroMQ, iOS, C#

Responsibilities

Productionize computer vision research for use in Niantic’s consumer client-server games and applications.
Discover ways to harden and robustify computer vision algorithms at intersection of research and engineering.
Build computer vision products into Niantic’s augmented reality platform from the bleeding edge of research innovations.

Qualifications
You have a MS or PhD in computer science or a related field, with focus on computer vision, robotics or deep learning.
You have practical experience developing algorithms and systems that leverage computer vision for augmented/mixed reality.
Extensive experience in C++ and OpenCV or other computer vision libraries.
Experience with any type of parallel programming (GPU/VPU, multi-core or distributed systems).
Plus If…

You have working knowledge computer vision geometry for 3D pose estimation and tracking.
You have experience building production computer vision or deep learning systems.
You have experience with a deep learning framework (Tensorflow, Caffe, PyTorch).
You have publications in a top tier conference such as CVPR, ICCV, ECCV, NIPS, ICLR, ICML.

MUST HAVE
MS or PHD specifically focused on: computer vision, robotics or deep learning.
2+ years experience
No candidates < 2 years regardless of their credentials
You have production work experience developing algorithms and systems that leverage computer vision for augmented/mixed reality
Very strong in C++ and OpenCV, have recently and actively used this on the job
Junior Candidates will be considered if they are exceptionally skilled in Computer Vision and have good work examples to show off
